1626:../Drivers/STM32_ExtMem_Manager/nor_sfdp/stm32_sfdp_data.c ****   /* Volatile or Non-Volatile Register and Write Enable Instruction for Status Register 1
1627:../Drivers/STM32_ExtMem_Manager/nor_sfdp/stm32_sfdp_data.c ****      The instruction 01h is typically used to write status register 1 which contains Block Protecti
1628:../Drivers/STM32_ExtMem_Manager/nor_sfdp/stm32_sfdp_data.c ****      and other bits. Status register 1 is written by the first data byte following the instruction 
1629:../Drivers/STM32_ExtMem_Manager/nor_sfdp/stm32_sfdp_data.c ****      The protection bits must be written to zero to enable writes/erases to the device.
